1 c. the Medical Director for the Oklahoma Perinatal
2 Quality Improvement Collaborative,
3 d. the Director of the Maternal and Child Health Service
4 of the State Department of Health,
5 e. the Chair of the Oklahoma Chapter of the Association
6 of Women's Health, Obstetric and Neonatal Nurses,
7 f. the Executive Director of the Southern Plains Tribal
8 Health Board,
9 g. the Director of the Oklahoma Perinatal Quality
10 Improvement Collaborative, and
11 h. the administrative program manager of the Maternal and
12 Child Health Service Perinatal and Reproductive Health
13 Division; and
14 2. Three of the members shall be appointed by the State
15 Commissioner of Health to serve for two-year terms and shall be
16 eligible for reappointment. The members shall be persons having
17 training and experience in matters related to maternal mortality and
18 severe maternal morbidity. The members shall be appointed from the
19 following positions:
20 a. a physician who is a member of the Oklahoma State
21 Medical Association or the Oklahoma Osteopathic
22 Association,
23 b. a maternal-fetal medicine physician, and
24
