1 c. an individual who has been affected by pregnancy-
2 related or pregnancy-associated deaths, severe
3 maternal morbidity, and/or lack of access to maternal
4 health care services.
5 B. Every two (2) years the Committee shall elect from among its
6 membership a chair and a vice chair. The Committee shall meet at
7 least quarterly and may meet more frequently as necessary as
8 determined by the chair.
9 C. The Maternal Mortality Review Committee may, as needed,
10 create advisory committees and assign members or non-members of the
11 Committee to participate.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
